The '''2003<U+2013>04 [[Croatian Cup]]''' was the 13th edition of [[Croatia]]'s premier [[association football]] knockout competition. [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] were the defending champions, and the cup was eventually won by [[NK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] on [[away goals rule]] after the aggregate score in the final tie was 1<U+2013>1 against [[NK Varteks|Varteks]]. This was the 7th Croatian cup title for Dinamo and Varteks' fourth final without a win.

